<ul><li> These actions have been confirmed as just expressly because they are beneficial. Thus the cornerstone of the Epicurean understanding of justice is instrumental, "utilitarian" (yet not, of course, in the sense of modern, economic, "upper-case" Utilitarianism), as it views justice  not as something inherently good in the abstract (Cf. [[Principal Doctrine 23]]), but as something useful for the benefits it confers.
</li></ul>
<ul><li> These confirmed actions are beneficial because they serve the needs of human association'><font color='#800000'>are</font></a>&nbsp;</p><br><p><a href='http://wiki.epicurism.info/iurl/index.php?title=Template:GED:are&amp;action=edit'><font color='#cc6600'>edit</font></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></span><span><p class='script150'><a href='http://wiki.epicurism.info/iurl/index.php?title=Template:GED:commonly' title='Dictionary empty: use link below:/→,2:/→,3:/What is confirmed by testimony,6:/for,7:the,8:needs,9:/of,10:/→,11:mutual,12:association,13:/→,15:to be,17:/has (the quality of),18:/[being],19:in,20:/the [domain],22:/→,23:/→,24:whether,26:/→,27:the same,28:/[may happen] to everyone,29:/→,30:/(or),33:/→,34:/→,35:/If,36:on the other hand,37:/→,38:/[one] establishes (some) [law],39:/→,40:/→,41:/[but it does not] result,42:/→,43:in,44:that which is,45:beneficial,46:/→,47:for,48:mutual,49:association,50:/[this] no longer,51:/→,52:/[has] the,53:/→,54:/→,55:/nature [of justice],56:/→,57:/And even if,58:/→,59:/that which is [beneficial],60:according to,61:/→,62:/justice [may change for the worse],63:/→,64:/→,65:while,66:/(for) some [time],67:/→,69:/preconception (of justice),70:/(it) may fit,71:/→,72:nonetheless,73:/(for) that,68:/[may have fit] the,70:/→,74:/→,76:/(it) was,77:just,78:to those who,79:/[do] not [agitate themselves],80:/→,81:/[with] empty [shouts],82:/→,83:/→,85:/plainly [look at],86:/→,87:the,88:facts,89:/→</interlinear>
